	<section id="changelog:umc">
		<title>Univention Management Console</title>

		<section id="changelog:umc:web">
			<title>Univention Management Console web interface</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The language sensitive sorting used in the grid via the <classname>Intl.Collator</classname> object is now used for other widgets as well (<u:bug>47195</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fixed a bug where the calendar widget would not display the date (<u:bug>47201</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Some errors were not displayed correctly in the <guilabel>Inform vendor</guilabel> dialogs (<u:bug>47133</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					An error in the conversion of SVG to PNG images has been resolved (<u:bug>47188</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:server">
			<title>Univention Management Console server</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fix memory leak caused by Python notifier traceback handling (<u:bug>47114</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					During a release update, Apache will serve the maintenance page instead of UMC (<u:bug>37223</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Enable bad password lockout policy in UMC (<u:bug>46978</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A problem with the SAML authentification which could lead to the UMC web interface becoming unresponsive has been fixed (<u:bug>46870</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:appcenter">
			<title>Univention App Center</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The command <command>univention-app logs</command> has been introduced for Docker Apps (<u:bug>46433</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The <command>univention-appcenter-listener-converter</command> has been fixed (<u:bug>47644</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fix memory leak caused by Python notifier traceback handling (<u:bug>47114</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Docker Apps no longer have a default for the attribute that controls which command is used to start the container.
					If not given, the command specified during the build of the image will now be used (<u:bug>42970</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The user <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> is used inside containers to run scripts (<u:bug>47340</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Timezone setup during docker app installations has been fixed (<u:bug>47373</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					For processing asynchronous notifications the new service <package>univention-appcenter-listener-converter</package> has been added (<u:bug>47315</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					A new &ucsUDL; module has been added to notify Apps when relevant objects change in LDAP (<u:bug>47265</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fix finding the wrong version in the App Cache.
					This issue could result in Apps being unregistered (<u:bug>47383</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fixed a bug that made the installation of certain Apps impossible when invoked from a remote server (<u:bug>47158</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Certain Apps could not be upgraded when installed on a non-Master system (<u:bug>47253</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Improved cache performance of the App Center (<u:bug>46821</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The command <command>univention-app</command> took every App from every UCS version into consideration.
					Now non-Docker Apps are excluded when the UCS version of the App and the one of the system do not match (<u:bug>47187</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:udmcli">
			<title>&ucsUDM; UMC modules and command line interface</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The property <property>Account is deactivated</property> of an user object was wrongly considered to be empty and resulted in a notification in the UMC (<u:bug>47199</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Ignore case during change of attribute <property>mailPrimaryAddress</property> on user objects (<u:bug>47415</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Add support for DNS <classname>NS</classname> records (<u:bug>32626</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:setup">
			<title>Modules for system settings / setup wizard</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Warn about already existing hostname when joining the system to the domain (<u:bug>46045</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Raise the required memory for UCS to 1 GB (<u:bug>45206</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fix memory leak caused by Python notifier traceback handling (<u:bug>47114</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Warn about unreachable repository servers when configuring the system (<u:bug>47105</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Detect potential problems with the domain join when configuring the system (<u:bug>42022</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Improve error messages of join failures (<u:bug>42366</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Clarification what kind of updates are installed on the last page of the &ucsUSS; (<u:bug>45931</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:update">
			<title>Software update module</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					During a release update &ucsUMC; will no longer be accessible.
					Instead a minimalistic web page informs about the progress of the update.
					UMC will be available again as soon as the update finished (<u:bug>37223</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:join">
			<title>Domain join module</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Exit samba slave PDC join scripts early if the system is not a &ucsUAS; slave (<u:bug>47234</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fix memory leak caused by Python notifier traceback handling (<u:bug>47114</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Add option to the <command>univention-join</command> tool for checking problems without altering the system (<u:bug>42022</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Improve error messages of join failures (<u:bug>42366</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					<command>univention-server-join</command> now checks and reports conflicts in name, role, MAC and IP address to provide better error feedback (<u:bug>42124</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:diagnostic">
			<title>System diagnostic module</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Only show <command>samba-tool dbcheck</command> errors as critical (<u:bug>46197</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:umc:other">
			<title>Other modules</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Fix UMC crashing on system time change (<u:bug>44222</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>
	</section>

	<section id="changelog:lib">
		<title>Univention base libraries</title>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The new &ucsUCRV; <envar>ldap/attributeoptions</envar> has been added to configure the <filename>slapd.conf</filename> <envar>attributeoptions</envar> parameter.
				The default for <envar>attributeoptions</envar> has changed from <literal>entry-</literal> to <literal>entry-,lang-</literal> (<u:bug>47246</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				Some debug message levels in LDAP overlays have been adjusted to more sensible values (<u:bug>47196</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				Protect code of <function>getMailFromMailOrUid</function> from execution on module load (<u:bug>47206</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</section>

	<section id="changelog:deployment">
		<title>Software deployment</title>
		<itemizedlist>
			<listitem><simpara>
				Show a warning and allow examination of the <filename>updater.log</filename> file in UMC if the last release update failed (<u:bug>47592</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				The progress of a release update is written to a status file so that the package <package>univention-maintenance-mode</package> may read it to update the progress accordingly (<u:bug>37223</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				Code for the deprecated UCS-2.x and UCS-3.x repository layout has been removed (<u:bug>36719</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
			<listitem><simpara>
				Network errors while trying to contact the update server do not result in a traceback anymore.
				Instead, a readable error message is shown (<u:bug>41536</u:bug>).
			</simpara></listitem>
		</itemizedlist>
	</section>

	<section id="changelog:service">
		<title>System services</title>

		<section id="changelog:service:postgresql">
			<title>PostgreSQL</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Use <command>deb-systemd-invoke stop "postgresql@$ver-*"</command> to prevent upgrading/removing server packages from stopping other major version clusters when running <command>systemd</command>.
					(Use <command>deb-systemd-invoke</command> instead of <command>invoke-rc.d</command>; Jessie's <command>invoke-rc.d</command> does not support service patterns.) (<u:bug>47511</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:service:docker">
			<title>Docker</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					During the initial setup by &ucsUSS; the package gets always installed inside the <command>chroot</command> environment.
					<command>systemd</command> is not yet used there, but the legacy SysV init scripts.
					Its stop action reports an error as the daemon is not running.
					This aborts the removal of the package, which is done when setting up a Base system (<u:bug>47194</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:service:saml">
			<title>SAML</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Raw service provider configurations can now be added to &ucsUDM; <classname>saml/serviceprovider</classname> objects.
					The configuration will be replicated to all domain IdP servers.
					In addition, the configuration option of <package>simplesamlphp</package> LDAP <property>get_attributes</property> is now done in LDAP.
					The current value set to the &ucsUCRV;s is migrated to the updated configuration (<u:bug>47309</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					When operating Apache without a separate <property>VirtualHost</property> entry for single sign-on, a <firstterm>rewrite</firstterm> rule in the scope of other configuration rules limited execution of further rewrite rules.
					This fix restricts the rewrite rule to the single sign-on directory (<u:bug>47241</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:service:dovecot">
			<title>Dovecot</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The PAM stack has been fixed to allow the login via username (<u:bug>47642</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:service:postfix">
			<title>Postfix</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					The PAM stack has been fixed to allow the login via username (<u:bug>47642</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

		<section id="changelog:service:nagios">
			<title>Nagios</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
