	<section id="changelog:win">
		<title>Services for Windows</title>

		<section id="changelog:win:samba">
			<title>Samba</title>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Update package <package>tevent</package> to version 0.9.36 as required by Samba 4.7.8 (<u:bug>47428</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Adjust default for &ucsUCRV; <envar>samba/ntlm/auth</envar> (<envar>ntlm auth</envar>) to <literal>ntlmv2-only</literal> (<u:bug>46782</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Share options in <package>univention-samba-local-config</package> have been fixed (<u:bug>46975</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Some scripts have been restored, that were deleted by a previous cleanup (<u:bug>47095</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					After a server password change restart all services of Samba, not just the AD/DC component (<u:bug>47638</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><para>
					Two new &ucsUCRV;s have been added to give more granular control over the behavior of the SYSVOL synchronization:
					<variablelist>
						<varlistentry>
							<term><envar>samba4/sysvol/sync/from_upstream/delete</envar></term>
							<listitem><simpara>
								control whether a downstream DC should delete local changes during the synchronization from the upstream DC (only useful in &ucsUAS; with unidirectional synchronization from upstream DC).
							</simpara></listitem>
						</varlistentry>
						<varlistentry>
							<term><envar>samba4/sysvol/sync/fix_gpt_ini</envar></term>
							<listitem><simpara>
								control whether old, redundant <filename>gpt.ini</filename> files should be deleted after the synchronization to the local SYSVOL directory (<u:bug>47576</u:bug>).
							</simpara></listitem>
						</varlistentry>
					</variablelist>
				</para></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Improved error message for &ucsUAS; slave join (<u:bug>47388</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
				<listitem><simpara>
					Continue <command>samba-tool dbcheck --fix</command> even if a modification failed (<u:bug>45982</u:bug>).
				</simpara></listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</section>

